survey_response.review_text: I am very thankful to Dr E Pavithra Balaji Mam, I am  more grateful and  appreciative her behaviour and humanity. Last 7 months back, it was diagnosed as PCOS and I was very upset and depressed about this issue enquired in my body. Thereafter, I found Pavithra mam on google web source and visited at her place Nungambakkam. I discussed all my problems and primarly, she has given a positive and moral support including medications. The place Nunambakkam was very far from my home and she suggested not to come here, I also do practice in Sugam Hospital, Tambaram. She took care  all my expenses spent for travelling from my home to Nungambakkam. Then, I visited to the suggested Hospital and met her for the issue. She always give moral support before prescription of the medicines, that I like most. After 7 months treatment, I am permanently cured from her treatment/medication, positive attutide and  moral support.  This time, no cysts seen in both the ovaries.  After God, I am again more thankful to Mam. The best thing is that she does not ask to go for more number of blood test, she suggested only the required test and saved our money. During this pandemic, I was stuck at my native place in north indian region and she always been in contact on phone at all the time. She always put attention on her patients and give positive response. Even if you are late on your scheduled time, she can wait and see her patients in all possible ways. I feel more proud to be a patient of Dr Pavithra Mam, and recommend to all those who are wasting their time here and there in other hospitals. Please visit at once and you will feel whatever I said, its 100% true. Once again thank to God who has chosen Dr Pavithra mam to resolve my medical problem. Thank you Mam.
